{"word":"ἀνταίρω","slug":"ἀνταίρω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀνταίρω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to raise against</i>, <el>χεῖράς τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>; so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> <i>to rise up against</i>, <el>τινί</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>; <el>πρός τι</el> or <el>τινα</el>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of a cliff, <i>to rise opposite to</i>, <el>πρὸς τὴν Λιβύην</el> <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}